---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

// Home — reassurance, a brief hint of what's here, an invitation.
// Story details live on /about; packages on /services.
---

<BaseLayout
  description="Yellow Legal Pad — financial coaching with Stacey. A quiet conversation, without judgment."
>
  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="welcome-heading">
    <div class="column">
      <h1 id="welcome-heading">
        The welcome mat is out.
      </h1>
      <p>
        If money feels complicated, or embarrassing, or just hard to
        look at, you don't need to know anything beforehand to start.
      </p>
      <!-- Image slot — pending warm abstract imagery from Stacey
           (legal pad and pen, desk scene, natural textures; no
           stock photos of women). See TODO_STACEY.md § Brand
           imagery. Uncomment alongside the Pass 459 follow-up.
      <figure class="page-image">
        <img src="/images/home-welcome.jpg" alt="" />
      </figure>
      -->
      <p>
        Yellow Legal Pad is a small coaching practice run by Stacey.
        She works with people navigating a transition &mdash;
        retirement, divorce, widowhood, a late start, caring for
        parents, a fresh chapter. No products to sell, no pressure.
      </p>
      <p>
        The name comes from Stacey's father. Every Friday, the same
        small desk in the hallway and the same yellow legal pad
        &mdash; one trusted advisor, thirty years of doing the
        sensible things without making them complicated. Stacey runs
        her practice the same way: plain language, a few things at a
        time, until the numbers stop feeling scary. <a href="/about">More about Stacey</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="column">
      <p>
        Most financial advice begins by suggesting you've fallen
        behind. Stacey doesn't.
      </p>
      <p class="pull-quote">
        They are not financially unintelligent. They are financially
        underserved. There is a profound difference.
      </p>
      <p>
        An industry that talks past people, charges too much, and
        assumes they should already know. Stacey starts somewhere
        else: a real conversation, in plain language, about your
        actual life. Whatever's in front of you now is what we work
        with.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="column">
      <p>
        Discovery Calls are free and take about twenty minutes. No
        script, no slideshow. Stacey will listen, ask a few questions,
        and say honestly whether she can help. There's no pressure
        to keep going.
      </p>
      <p>
        The best time to start was thirty years of Fridays ago. The
        second best time is today.
      </p>
      <p style="margin-top: 1.75rem;">
        <a href="/contact" class="cta">Book a free Discovery Call</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
